v3.5.1: Westminster RMS parser fixes, manual person re-routing, sort persistence

RMS Import — Westminster Draft Copy parser
- Fix Event Information block embedded mid-list in Other Person(s).
  Westminster prints Event Info at the bottom of page 1 between Person 1
  and Persons 2..N (which continue on page 2); parser was terminating at
  the Event Info section boundary and silently dropping persons 2..N.
  Now scans past the Event Info block for additional "Person\n\d+" entries
  and parses them with the same parsePersonBlock helper.
- Add bare "By Officer X Y BadgeNum" pattern to narrative-header detection
  (in addition to the existing "Original/Supplemental Report Narrative By"
  INFORM RMS pattern). Westminster narratives were previously dropped
  because the regex didn't match the bare form.
- Tighten the embedded Reporting Employee skip in narrative collection:
  skip the column-header line ("Reporting Role ... Position/Title ...")
  and the concatenated value line ("ReportingOfficerTravis Morgan 2511")
  rather than blindly advancing on whitespace.
- Phone field hardening: reject phone values that look like field labels
  ("Phone 2", "Employer", etc.) when the source field is empty. Was
  promoting "Phone 2" label text into the Suspect's phone slot because it
  contained a digit.

RMS Import — Manual person re-routing
- Each parsed person card on the RMS Import detail view now exposes a
  "Move to:" action row (Suspect / Victim / Witness / Involved) so users
  can override the auto-route classification.
- The move is idempotent: prior auto-routed copies (matched on name +
  rmsSource) are removed from Suspects/Victims/Witnesses/InvolvedPersons
  before the new entry is added to the chosen tab.
- Each target tab gets a schema-correct record (identifiers/firearms for
  Suspects, injury/property photos for Victims, statement for Witnesses,
  role/relationship/notes for Involved Persons).
- Auto-activates the Involved Persons module on the case when moving
  someone there.
- Selection is persisted on the report (person.routedTo / routedToTarget)
  and surfaces as a green badge on the card so overrides are visible.
- Refreshes loadSuspects / loadVictims / loadWitnesses / loadInvolvedPersons
  / renderInvolvedPersons after the move; re-renders the active tab via
  renderTabContent(currentTab || 'rmsImport') — fixes "undefined Module"
  fall-through that occurred when renderTabContent was called with no arg.

Dashboard — Active Investigations sort persistence
- setInvestigationsFilter(filter) duplicated the filtering logic from
  filterInvestigations() but skipped the sort step, then called
  updateActiveInvestigationsTable directly. On every dashboard load the
  init script calls setInvestigationsFilter(savedFilter) at line 3903, so
  rows were rebuilt unsorted while the header arrow still showed the
  saved direction — looking like the sort wasn't persistent.
- filterInvestigations() is now the single source of truth: ported the
  active/closed/closed-arrest custom-status category rollup logic into
  it so it covers every filter case the dropdown produces.
- setInvestigationsFilter(filter) now updates currentInvestigationsFilter,
  persists it, sets the title, then delegates to filterInvestigations()
  so sort + filter stay in sync.

Internal
- .gitignore: also exclude _test_*.js (scratch parser test harnesses).
